nodes.documentation: -- APPLICATION ENTRY POINTS --
Allows the owner to change the name of the contract
nodes.name: setName

nodes.documentation: Allows the owner to change the symbol of the contract
nodes.name: setSymbol

nodes.documentation:
Allows the owner to change the decimals of the counter in case
they want to support an ERC-20 token with less decimals than 18
Only works prior to money being in the contract
nodes.name: setDecimals

nodes.documentation:
Allows the owner to change the revenue cost on selling as a percent
Only works prior to money being in the contract
nodes.name: setSellRevenuePercent

nodes.documentation:
Allows the owner to change the decimals of the counter in case
they want to support an ERC-20 token with less decimals than 18
Only works prior to there being money in the contract
nodes.name: setCounter

nodes.documentation: Converts all incoming counter to tokens for the caller
nodes.name: buy

nodes.documentation: Converts all incoming counter to tokens for the caller
nodes.name: buyERC20

nodes.documentation:
Fallback function to handle counter that was sent straight to the contract.
Causes tokens to be purchased.
Create revenue without purchasing tokens
nodes.name: donate

nodes.documentation: Liquifies tokens to counter.
nodes.name: sell

nodes.documentation:
Transfer tokens from the caller to a new holder.
Transfering ownership of tokens requires settling outstanding dividends
and transfering them back. You can therefore send 0 tokens to this contract to
trigger your withdraw.
nodes.name: transfer

nodes.documentation:
Transfer `tokens` from the `from` account to the `to` account

    * The calling account must already have sufficient tokens approve(...)-d
for spending from the `from` account and
- From account must have sufficient balance to transfer
- Spender must have sufficient allowance to transfer
- 0 value transfers are allowed

    * Implementation taken from ERC20 reference
nodes.name: transferFrom

nodes.documentation:
Returns the amount of tokens approved by the owner that can be
transferred to the spender's account

    * Implementation taken from ERC20 reference
nodes.name: allowance

nodes.documentation:
Token owner can approve for `spender` to transferFrom(...) `tokens`
from the token owner's account. The `spender` contract function
`receiveApproval(...)` is then executed
nodes.name: approveAndCall

nodes.documentation:
Method to view the current Counter stored in the contract
Example: totalDestinationBalance()
nodes.name: counterBalance

nodes.documentation: Retrieve the name of the token.
nodes.name: name

nodes.documentation: Retrieve the symbol of the token.
nodes.name: symbol

nodes.documentation: Retrieve the decimals of the token.
nodes.name: decimals

nodes.documentation: Retrieve the spread percent applied upon selling
nodes.name: sellRevenuePercent

nodes.documentation: Retrieve the total token supply.
nodes.name: totalTokens

nodes.documentation: Retrieve the tokens owned by the caller.
nodes.name: myTokens

nodes.documentation: Retrieve the token balance of any single address.
nodes.name: balanceOf

nodes.documentation: Convert X tokens to Y counter
nodes.name: tokensToCounter

nodes.documentation: Convert X counter to Y tokens
nodes.name: counterToTokens

nodes.documentation: Calculate the cost of selling X tokens
nodes.name: revenueCost

nodes.documentation:
Owner can transfer out any accidentally sent ERC20 tokens

    * Implementation taken from ERC20 reference
nodes.name: transferAnyERC20Token
